Title : David Floyd
Text : '''David W. Floyd''' (born October 2, 1951 in [[Louisville, Kentucky]]) is an [[United States|American]] politician and a former [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] member of the [[Kentucky House of Representatives]] for District 50. Floyd dropped out after filing for re-election in 2016 when Republican Chad McCoy challenged Floyd in the primary<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kentucky.com/news/politics-government/article57743088.html|title=GOP state Rep. David Floyd won’t seek re-election|last=Co|first=Kentucky Legislative Research|website=kentucky|language=en|access-date=2019-05-12}}</ref>.  Floyd was later appointed to be KY House Chief of Staff in 2018, after which controversy arose over his campaign contributions to his new boss Speaker David Osborne who appointed him<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kyrecord.com/did-republican-david-floyd-buy-a-115000-a-year-job-at-the-expense-of-taxpayers/|title=Did Republican David Floyd Buy A $115,000 A Year Job At The Expense of Taxpayers?|last=Report|first=Ky Record Staff|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-12}}</ref>.  Floyd was known for pushing to abolish the Death Penalty in Kentucky even though his home district of Nelson County and the state overwhelmingly supports the Death Penalty in capital murder cases<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.courier-journal.com/story/news/politics/2016/03/09/bill-abolish-death-penalty-ky-defeated/81493874/|title=Bill to abolish death penalty in Ky defeated|website=The Courier-Journal|language=en|access-date=2019-05-12}}</ref>. {{Infobox state representative
